item.title: Long road to economic recovery: RBA
item.description: The Reserve Bank of Australia warns further outbreaks of coronavirus will threaten the country’s economic recovery, potentially pushing high levels of unemployment into 2021.

item.title: Broncos legend virus breach
item.description: Broncos legend Allan Langer and two other staffers have been banned from tonight’s match against the South Sydney Rabbitohs after the trio attended a Brisbane pub, breaching the NRL’s strict biosecurity rules.

item.title: Why the gold price is soaring
item.description: The gold price is expected to keep soaring as the factors driving it higher won’t likely change any time soon, with one analyst tipping it could hit $US3000 an ounce.

item.title: Last minute Qld border ‘glitch’
item.description: Police fear changes to the border declaration online system may not be ready in time for Queensland’s 1am border curfew, potentially adding extra wait time to already lengthy queues.

item.title: PM’s warning on big vaccine risk
item.description: Australia is gearing up to manufacture and supply coronavirus vaccines if they are developed, Scott Morrison says.

item.title: Fifita shows off ugly finger injury
item.description: Cronulla prop Andrew Fifita has revealed he is still two weeks away from a comeback after sharing graphic pictures of his finger injury on social media.

item.title: IS video urges Aussie fire attacks
item.description: Prime Minister Scott Morrison has confirmed a “sick” video has been released by Islamic State encouraging new recruits to set fire to bushland in Australia.

item.title: ‘Don’t put innocent lives at risk’
item.description: Queensland’s deputy premier has made an impassioned plea to protesters planning on demonstrating this weekend, saying it’s “selfish” behaviour that puts the lives of innocent people at risk.

item.title: VCE students to be ‘individually assessed’
item.description: Victorian Year 12 students will be assessed individually for their VCE scores and ATAR rankings, in sweeping changes that will take into account the difficult impact of COVID-19.

item.title: ‘Chaos’ at border amid rush to enter
item.description: It was “chaos” at the New South Wales and Victoria border on Thursday as returning residents rushed to enter the state before the latest wave of COVID-19 restrictions came into force.
